3 Section 1. Section 20-1-501, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "20-1-501. Recognition of American Indian cultural heritage -- legislative intent. (1) It is the
5 constitutionally declared policy of this state to recognize the distinct and unique cultural heritage of American
6 Indians and to be committed in its educational goals to the preservation of their cultural heritage.
7 (2) It is the intent of the legislature that in accordance with Article X, section 1(2), of the Montana
8 constitution:
9 (a) every Montanan, whether Indian or non-Indian, learn about the distinct and unique heritage of
10 American Indians in a culturally responsive manner; and
11 (b) every educational agency work cooperatively in consultation with Montana tribes or those tribes
12 that are in close proximity, when providing instruction or when implementing an educational goal or adopting a
13 rule related to the education of each Montana citizen, to include information specific to the cultural heritage and
14 contemporary contributions of American Indians, with particular emphasis on Montana Indian tribal groups and
15 governments.
16 (3) It is also the intent of this part, predicated on the belief that all school personnel should have an
17 understanding and awareness of Indian tribes to help them relate effectively with Indian students and parents,
18 that educational agencies provide means by which school personnel will gain an understanding of and
19 appreciation for the American Indian people."
20
